{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, at 16 layers, the ACC values are 0.18467, 0.3293, and 0.26475, respectively.",
    "On the other hand, the MultiCGCN model exhibits improved performance as the number of network layers increases up to 4 layers.",
    "Subsequently, its performance begins to decline with further layer increments, but it still achieves ACC values of 0.87329, 0.79646, and 0.82807 on the Citeseer, DBLP, and SDBLP datasets, respectively, even at 16 layers.",
    "This demonstrates that the multi-channel graph neural network model with residual connections effectively alleviates overfitting and oversmoothing phenomena.",
    "The DeepMCGCN model consistently shows an upward trend in performance with an increase in the number of network layers, providing evidence of the effectiveness of the approach presented in this paper."
  ]
}